<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/21965967-amber"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1449092263i/21965967._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/21965967-amber">Amber</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I read the book and then watched the movie the next day, and in both, my impression is that she&apos;s intrigued by him because he doesn&apos;t take her up on h<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I read the book and then watched the movie the next day, and in both, my impression is that she's intrigued by him because he doesn't take her up on her early offer of sex, which makes him not like most other men. Like everyone is telling Pat, she needs a friend, and here's this guy who likes her enough to ask her out to the diner, but apparently doesn't want to sleep with her, at least not right away. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
